In [[textual criticism]], an '''exemplar''' is the text used to produce another text. In the study of the history of a text an especially important exemplar is that which precedes any split in the tradition of that text, that is, before significant textual variations occur in different versions--such an exemplar is called an [[Archetype (disambiguation)|archetype]].


