During [[heterosexual]] [[anal sex]], splash conception occurs when [[semen]] containing [[spermatozoon|sperm]] migrates from the [[anus]], across the [[perineum]], to the [[labia (genitalia)|labia]], and subsequently into the [[vagina]], causing the fertilization of an [[ovum]] followed by [[Conception (biology)|conception]] or [[pregnancy]].  This migration does not occur by virtue of the spermatozoa's tail propulsion, but rather due to gravity or other kinetic forces (such as that of a penis pulling out of an anus and dragging semen left on the tip, or being expelled from the anus due to said penis's recent ejaculation, across the perineum and onto the labia.

